                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/2600</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-09T12:00:00+09:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 9, 1917, noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My telegram June 8, 10 p.m. The Press today shows general irritation at the
                    communication made by Reinsch to China which is viewed as interference in the
                    latter’s internal politics and a further indication of objectionable activity of
                    the Legation at Peking. The Foreign Office assumed that our proposal
                    contemplated joint as well as identic representation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wheeler</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
